{"questionId":"20390","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> intersect at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> has a gradient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and is a tangent to the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the equation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>45</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math> (in any order)&nbsp;into an appropriate equation&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo